<body><div class=WordSection1>
<div class="brand">📚 ENGLISH CODING · 영어코딩</div>
<h1>🤖 AI001 Week 2 — English Worksheet</h1>
<p><strong>Topic:</strong> Good Prompts vs Bad Prompts · <strong>Course:</strong> AI Coding with Replit Agent · <strong>Time:</strong> about 45 minutes</p>
<p>The AI does what it <strong>reads</strong>, not what you imagine. If your prompt is vague, the AI guesses, and the result is random. A good prompt has three things: it is <strong>specific</strong>, it has a <strong>clear outcome</strong>, and it gives <strong>constraints</strong> (what to do and what not to do).</p>
<hr />
<h2>1 · Predict 🔮</h2>
<p>Read each prompt. Before the AI builds it, write what kind of result you expect — and how <em>sure</em> you are that you will get what you pictured.</p>
<pre><code>Make a cool web page.
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Will every student who types this get the same thing? Why or why not?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<pre><code>Make an about-me page.
</code></pre>
<p><strong>This is better than "cool web page". But what is still missing?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<pre><code>Make an about-me page with three sections — name, age,
and hobbies — in pastel colors.
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Which of the three rules (specific / clear outcome / constraints) does this prompt use?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h2>2 · Spot the Weak Prompt 🐛</h2>
<p>Each prompt below is too weak to give a good result. Read what the student <strong>wanted</strong>, then rewrite the prompt so it is specific, has a clear outcome, and gives constraints. Then explain what was missing.</p>
<p><strong>Prompt A</strong> — The student wanted a <strong>calculator</strong> with number buttons, the four math buttons, a result screen, and a reset button.</p>
<pre><code>Make a calculator.
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Hint:</strong> list the buttons and the screen. Add a color theme as a constraint.</p>
<p><strong>Write a strong prompt:</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>What was missing from the first one?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>Prompt B</strong> — The student wanted a <strong>to-do list</strong> page, but written in a way the AI can picture clearly.</p>
<pre><code>Make something to write my tasks.
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Hint:</strong> say it is a web page, name the parts (input box, add button, list), and describe how it should look.</p>
<p><strong>Write a strong prompt:</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>What was missing from the first one?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>Prompt C</strong> — The student wanted a page, but <strong>without</strong> a dark background and <strong>without</strong> tiny text (those hurt their eyes).</p>
<pre><code>Make a nice page but not ugly.
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Hint:</strong> "not ugly" tells the AI nothing. Use real constraints: "don't use a dark background", "don't make the text small".</p>
<p><strong>Write a strong prompt:</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>What was missing from the first one?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h2>3 · Three Prompts, One Task 📸</h2>
<p>Pick <strong>one</strong> task — for example, "a page about my favorite animal". Write it <strong>three ways</strong> and run each in Replit:</p>
<ol>
<li>A <strong>bad</strong> prompt (vague, like "make a page").</li>
<li>A <strong>medium</strong> prompt (a bit more detail).</li>
<li>A <strong>good</strong> prompt (specific + clear outcome + constraints).</li>
</ol>
<p>Look at the three results side by side. Send a <strong>photo or video</strong> of the three results, then explain the difference. Use these sentence starters — write 4 to 6 sentences total.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>My task was to build …</p>
<p>My bad prompt was … and the result …</p>
<p>My good prompt added … so the result …</p>
<p>The biggest difference between bad and good was …</p>
<p>A constraint I used was …</p>
<p>Next time I will always remember to …</p>
</blockquote>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h2>4 · Rewrite "Make a Game" 🗒️</h2>
<p>For homework you will turn <strong>"make a game"</strong> into three levels of prompts. Plan them here first.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Level 1 (bad):</p>
<p>Level 2 (medium):</p>
<p>Level 3 (good — specific, clear outcome, constraints):</p>
</blockquote>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h3>Submit ✅</h3>
<p>Send this worksheet + photos (or a video) of your three results + your three prompts to teacher on KakaoTalk.</p>
